description: Flag that should be enabled when the current dataview is missing.

description: Callback that is called when the user changes the currently selected dataview.

Callback that is called when the user edits the current data view via flyout.
The first parameter is the updated data view stub without fetched fields

children.label: onAddField
description:
Callback that is called when the user clicks the add runtime field option.
Also works as a flag to show the add runtime field button.

children.label: onDataViewCreated
description:
Callback that is called when the user creates a new data view through the picker menu.
The first parameter is the created data view
Also works as a flag to show the create dataview button.

description: Makes the picker disabled by disabling the popover trigger

description: Optional callback when data view picker is closed

interfaces.label: FilterItemsProps
description:
Properties for the filter items component, which will render a single filter pill for every filter that is sent in
as part of the `Filter[]` property.

children.label: filters
description: Array of filters that will be rendered as filter pills

children.label: readOnly
description:
Optional property that controls whether or not clicking the filter pill opens a popover *and* whether
or not the `x` button to remove the filter is rendered.

children.label: onFiltersUpdated
description: If not read only, this is called whenever a filter is removed and/or updated

children.label: indexPatterns
description: A list of all dataviews that are used for the filters

children.label: intl

children.label: timeRangeForSuggestionsOverride

children.label: filtersForSuggestions
description: adds additional filters to be used for suggestions

children.label: hiddenPanelOptions

children.label: suggestionsAbstraction
description: Array of suggestion abstraction that controls the render of the field
